         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12/4/81 ¶  ¶ You asked me repeatedly, dear Sir Joseph, for seeds of Epacrideae. ¶  Herewith a few. But the seeds of drupaceous Epacrideae must be  ¶ enucleated ¶ , as the small seeds could not burst t...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.04.12a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 300.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12/4/81<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation: 'JS'.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You asked me repeatedly, dear Sir Joseph, for seeds of <name key="Epacrideae">Epacrideae</name>.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">See, for example, J. Hooker to M, 11 July 1869 and May 14 1870, and M's responses to letters not found, for example, M to J. Hooker, September 1869. No such request occurs in surviving letters from Hooker in 1879 or 1880.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Herewith a few. But the seeds of drupaceous <name key="Epacrideae">Epacrideae</name> must be <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">enucleated</hi>
               </seg>, as the small seeds could not burst the hard putamen. Nature helps in this way, by the bush-fires, which scorch the endocarp. I found a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">rasp</hi>
               </seg> the best implement to set free the seeds.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There is no signature, but the letter is in M's handwriting.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Epacrideae">Epacrideae</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
